{"id":1077,"date":"2021-06-01T12:32:54","date_gmt":"2021-06-01T16:32:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhide.net\/?p=1077"},"modified":"2021-06-02T12:08:27","modified_gmt":"2021-06-02T16:08:27","slug":"capitalism-wont-thrive-on-value-investing-alone-just-published-hbr-org-oped","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/bhide.net\/wordpress_files\/index.php\/capitalism-wont-thrive-on-value-investing-alone-just-published-hbr-org-oped\/","title":{"rendered":"Capitalism Won\u2019t Thrive on Value Investing Alone (just published HBR.org oped)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>First oped in more than a year (when I was maniacally trying to get my medical innovation course done&#8230;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p><p>Trigger warning: starts with a suicide and more personal than my usual fare<\/p> \u00a0 <figure style=\"width: 522px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/hbr.org\/2021\/06\/capitalism-wont-thrive-on-value-investing-alone\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"522\" height=\"294\" class=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/hbr.org\/resources\/images\/article_assets\/2021\/06\/May21_28_93543493.jpg\"\/><\/a><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">by Amar Bhid\u00e9 June 01, 2021<\/figcaption><\/figure> <p>https:\/\/hbr.org\/2021\/06\/capitalism-wont-thrive-on-value-investing-alone<\/p><span class=\"summary-header font-bold\">Summary.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/span>Investors fall into two camps: value investors, who base decisions on a careful analysis of revenues and costs, looking for steady performance, and growth investors, who place bets on risky projects with very high potential payoffs. A capitalist economy needs both kinds \u2014 those willing to back transformational ventures as well as those who reward prudence and thrift.\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>First oped in more than a year (when I was maniacally trying to get my medical innovation course done&#8230; Trigger<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_stat